With the proper `RoomEntity` implementation (`hashCode` and `equals` implemented for `roomName`), you can reduce the code way more. All you really need is:

	List&lt;RoomEntity&gt; rooms1 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
	List&lt;RoomEntity&gt; rooms2 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
	rooms1.retainAll(rooms2);

`#retainAll()` keeps only the entities which are present in both lists. It compares entities using the `equals()` method. 

Here is a full example code:

    public class Test {
    
    	public static void main(String[] args) throws ParseException {
    		List&lt;RoomEntity&gt; rooms1 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    		List&lt;RoomEntity&gt; rooms2 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    		List&lt;RoomEntity&gt; rooms3 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    
    		Collections.copy(rooms3, rooms1); // only necessary if you don&#39;t want to change rooms1
    		rooms1.retainAll(rooms2);
    	}
    
    }
    
    class RoomEntity {
    	private String roomName;
    
    	public String getRoomName() {
